IUP Track & Field Preview: 2017 PSAC Outdoor Championships

2017 PSAC OUTDOOR CHAMPIONSHIPS

Thursday-Saturday, May 4-6, 2017

Bloomsburg, Pa. | Robert B. Redman Stadium

Meet Website | Schedule of Events | Live Results |

Men's Starters | Women's Starters

THE CHAMPIONSHIPS AT A GLANCE

The Crimson Hawks men's and women's track & field are set to compete in the 2017 Pennsylvania State Athletic Conference (PSAC) Outdoor Championships this weekend in Bloomsburg. The Championships open up on Thursday, May 4 and run through Saturday, May 6 at Robert B. Redman Stadium.

STORYLINES / WHAT TO WATCH FOR

* IUP will send a total of 30 student-athletes to Bloomsburg to compete in 24 combined events; 11 different Crimson Hawks will compete in two individual events

* Seven total athletes are ranked in the top three in nine individual events, including five total top seeds; Lizzy Cunningham (Hastings, Pa. /Northern Cambria) is ranked first in both the 800 meters and 400 hurdles

* Additional No. 1 rankings include Austin Cooper (King of Prussia, Pa. /Upper Merion ) in the 800 meters, Greg Beaudette (Johnston, R.I./Bishop Hendricken) in the 10,000 meters, and DJ Horton (Kane, Pa./Kane Area) in the pole vault

* The IUP women also have a pair of relays that head into the weekend ranked in the top three - the 4x100 and the 4x400

* Cooper and Horton look to repeat as individual champions, as Cooper won the 1500 and Horton the pole vault at the 2016 PSAC Outdoor Championships

* The first event for IUP is the women's and men's 10K on Thursday night starting at 8 p.m.; Field events begin Friday at noon and Saturday at 11 a.m.
